    // - A threshold graph on N vertices is defined by a binary string of N-1 bits
    // - Sorted degree sequence uniquely identifies a threshold graph (up to isomorphism)
    // - Perfect for this problem: degree sequence is permutation-invariant (handles shuffle)
    //   and provides a rich N-dimensional feature for matching (handles noise)
    //
    // Strategy:
    // 1. Choose smallest N such that we have enough distinguishable threshold graphs
    //    AND the degree sequences remain separable under noise
    // 2. Greedily select M threshold graphs with maximum pairwise degree-seq distance
    // 3. Decode by matching sorted degree sequence under noise model

    int N;

